    "body": "\r\nCurrently develop share/spack/setups.{csh,sh} puts just the micro-architecture specific (i.e. ivybridge) paths in `MODULEPATH,` anything built with the generic (i.e. x86_64) architecture thus cannot be accessed via module load, etc.   This patch adds them both to modulepath.  It finds the generic architecture by scanning the output of `spack arch --known-targets`",
    "performed_via_github_app": null
